placemark.name: Chance
placemark.latest_position:
Chance's last known position

Sadly in May 2016, Chance disappeared in an area of South Lanarkshire, not far from where she was originally tagged. She has not been seen or heard from since.

placemark.name: Holly
placemark.latest_position:
Holly's last known position

In mid-October 2015, Holly's satellite tag data suggested she had died in area of upland farmland and forestry to the north east of Glasgow. Despite a thorough search of the area we were unable to locate her body, and therefore do not know the reasons for her death. We will of course provide an update if any further information comes to light.

placemark.name: Elwood
placemark.latest_position:
Elwood's last known position

In August 2016, barely a month after fledging, Elwood suddenly disappeared in an area of managed moorland in the Northern Monadhliaths. He has not been seen or heard from since.

placemark.name: Carroll
placemark.latest_position:
Carroll's last known position

Sadly, on the 26th January 2017, the body of a satellite tagged hen harrier was found near to Carroll's last known location by a local landowner who immediately reported it to the local authorities. The body was retrieved with full cooperation and assistance from the landowner and local wildlife crime officers, and a post-mortem examination confirmed that Carroll had died naturally as the result of a parasitic infection. Incredibly, it also showed that she was carrying two shot pellets lodged under healed wounds, indicating that she had survived being shot at some point earlier in her lifetime.

placemark.name: Bonny
placemark.latest_position:
Bonny's last known position

Bonny's tag last transmitted on 14 December 2016 from an area of moorland a few kilometres to the east of Geltsdale. No data has been received since. While we have no information to suggest what might have happened, we believe it most likely that he has died. Despite a search of the area, no body was found.

placemark.name: Beater
placemark.latest_position:
Beater's last known position

No data have been received from Beater since 14 November 2016. Beater's last known location was on an area of upland pasture and while we have no information to suggest anything illegal has happened, we believe it is most likely that he has died. Despite a search of the area, no body was found, so unfortunately we will never know the cause of death.

placemark.name: Donald
placemark.latest_position:
Donald's last known position

Sadly, not long after his arrival in France, the data from Donald's tag showed that he had stopped moving, indicating that he had died. He was traced to an area of scrubby farmland but by the time our team could reach him, the battery in his tag had run down, meaning the signal had stopped. Despite a thorough search of the area, his body couldn't be found, so we will never know the cause of death.

placemark.name: Hermione
placemark.latest_position:
Hermione's last known position

On 28th September it became clear from the data received that Hermione had stopped moving. In just a few days, RSPB Investigation staff located her body and the transmitter, only a few kilometres from her nest it was clear that she had died naturally, and her remains had been partially eaten. Sad though this is, many young harriers do not survive their first winter, with starvation or predation a regular cause of death.

placemark.name: Calluna
placemark.latest_position:
Calluna's last known position

Sadly, less that three weeks after fledging, Calluna's tag suddenly stopped transmitting and she disappeared in an area of moorland managed for driven grouse shooting. She has not been seen or heard from since.

placemark.name: Tony
placemark.latest_position:
Tony's last known position

Tony's tag was functioning perfectly, with his last known fix on 22nd October on a peninsular west of Cambados, before transmissions abruptly and inexplicably stopped and we haven't received any transmissions since.

placemark.name: Sirius
placemark.latest_position:
Sirius' last known position

On 11th October, our Investigations team monitoring Sirius' tag saw that he had stopped moving. The team carried out a search and were able to locate and recover his body from a hillside near Loch Lomond. We are awaiting his final results from post mortem tests.

placemark.name: Manu
placemark.latest_position:
Manu's last known position

Manu's tag was functioning perfectly, with his last known fix on 18th October on Blenkinsopp Common, Northumberland before transmissions abruptly and inexplicably stopped and we haven't received any transmissions since.

placemark.name: Aalin
placemark.latest_position:
Aalin's last known position

Aalin's tag suddenly stopped transmitting and she disappeared in an area of moorland managed for driven grouse shooting around Ruabon Mountain near Wrexham. She has not been seen or heard from since.

placemark.name: Eric
placemark.latest_position:
Eric's last known position

Eric's tag showed he made a sudden and unexpected journey eastwards, away from the islands and out into the North Sea. Data from later that day showed that he had gone down in the water, and shortly afterwards the tag ceased transmitting. All the evidence suggests Eric drowned.

Latest position

After leaving his nest area, Thoth has headed over to Ireland, and has been exploring all over. Currently he is in the region of Sligo.

placemark.latest_position:

Marci has been exploring Aberdeenshire.

placemark.name: Vulcan
placemark.latest_position:
Latest position

Vulcan is a young male from Northumberland. He is one for finding an area and sticking to it. He moved from Northumberland to the Peak District and then on to Salisbury Plain.

placemark.name: Rain
placemark.latest_position:
Latest position

Rain spent a large part of her young life in and around the north Pennines, near the A66 whereby she has become rather site faithful. She has been spending a lot of her time with one of her sisters.

placemark.name: Nyx
placemark.latest_position:
Latest position

Nyx has travelled from the Forest of Bowland to the Yorkshire Dales National Park, on to Bolton, Burnley and back to Yorkshire Dales National Park before heading on to Northumberland.

placemark.name: Arthur
placemark.latest_position:
Latest position

Arthur's heart well and truly belongs in the peaks. He began to wander from a favourite site in the Peak District with the onset of cooler autumnal temperatures. Arthur is still unsettled and despite a quick rove across to Wales he decided to return to England and is currently exploring the Yorkshire Dales.
